docs.abstract: Merck and Pfizer will soon debut prescription pills to treat Covid-19. And more drugs are on the way.
docs.snippet: Merck and Pfizer will soon debut prescription pills to treat Covid-19. And more drugs are on the way.
docs.lead_paragraph: As the world worries that the Omicron coronavirus variant may cause a surge of cases and weaken vaccines, drug developers have some encouraging news: Two new Covid-19 pills are coming soon, and are expected to work against all versions of the virus.

headline.main: New Covid Pills Offer Hope as Omicron Looms

docs.abstract: Some laboratory studies suggest that molnupiravir can insert errors in DNA, which could in theory harm a developing fetus, sperm cells or children.
docs.snippet: Some laboratory studies suggest that molnupiravir can insert errors in DNA, which could in theory harm a developing fetus, sperm cells or children.
docs.lead_paragraph: A new Covid-19 pill from Merck has raised hopes that it could transform the landscape of treatment options for Americans at high risk of severe disease at a time when the Omicron variant of the coronavirus is driving a surge of cases in highly vaccinated European countries.

headline.main: Mercks Covid Pill Might Pose Risks for Pregnant Women
headline.print_headline: As Mercks Covid Pill Awaits Approval, Some Scientists Worry It Might Alter Human DNA

docs.abstract: Samantha Lewis is relearning some basic aspects of her daily life after struggling with brain fog and other lingering symptoms for more than a year since being infected by the virus.
docs.snippet: Samantha Lewis is relearning some basic aspects of her daily life after struggling with brain fog and other lingering symptoms for more than a year since being infected by the virus.
docs.lead_paragraph: AURORA, Ill.  There is sobering evidence of Samantha Lewiss struggle with long Covid on her bathroom mirror.

headline.main: Cognitive Rehab: One Patients Painstaking Path Through Long Covid Therapy
headline.print_headline: An Excruciating Journey Back From Long Covid

byline.original: By Pam Belluck and Alex Wroblewski

docs.abstract: The Omicron variant turned my trip home from South Africa into a nightmare episode of conflicting public health orders that often seemed to have little connection to science.
docs.snippet: The Omicron variant turned my trip home from South Africa into a nightmare episode of conflicting public health orders that often seemed to have little connection to science.
docs.lead_paragraph: HALIFAX, Nova Scotia  In early November, I flew to southern Africa to report a series of stories about the state of the Covid-19 pandemic in the region, including one about the remarkable work being done to stanch the emergence of new coronavirus variants. My last afternoon there, South African scientists announced the discovery of the Omicron variant. Hours later, I got on a plane in Johannesburg to head home to Canada.

headline.main: I Got Caught in a Pandemic Panic 2 Years Into Covid. It Felt Like Day 1.
headline.print_headline: Caught in the Whirlwind of a Panic

docs.abstract: The country regards children as crucial in its quest for herd immunity, but some parents, worried about the vaccines safety, are pushing back.
docs.snippet: The country regards children as crucial in its quest for herd immunity, but some parents, worried about the vaccines safety, are pushing back.
docs.lead_paragraph: As the rest of the world struggles to vaccinate adults in the face of a threat from a new coronavirus variant, China has embarked on an ambitious campaign that it says will give the country better protection against Covid-19: full inoculation of 160 million of its youngest citizens by the end of the year.

headline.main: In Its War on Covid-19, China Calls on Little Inoculated Warriors
headline.print_headline: China Goads Littlest Ones To Take Shot

docs.abstract: Mark Meadows, Mr. Trumps former chief of staff, said in his new book that the weakened presidents blood oxygen level reached 86 during a harrowing fight against the coronavirus.
docs.snippet: Mark Meadows, Mr. Trumps former chief of staff, said in his new book that the weakened presidents blood oxygen level reached 86 during a harrowing fight against the coronavirus.
docs.lead_paragraph: President Donald J. Trumps blood oxygen level sank to a precariously low level after he announced that he had tested positive for the coronavirus last year, according to a new book by Mark Meadows, his former chief of staff.

headline.main: Trumps Blood Oxygen Level in Covid Bout Was Dangerously Low, Former Aide Says

docs.abstract: In a comparison of seven different brands, researchers found that most shots give a strong boost, even in mix-and-match combinations.
docs.snippet: In a comparison of seven different brands, researchers found that most shots give a strong boost, even in mix-and-match combinations.
docs.lead_paragraph: People looking for a booster shot of a Covid-19 vaccine probably dont need to fret about what brand it is: Many combinations of shots are likely to provide strong protection, according to a large new study.

headline.main: Most Covid Vaccines Will Work as Boosters, Study Suggests
headline.print_headline: Study Says Most Vaccines Work as Boosters, Even in Mix and Match Combinations

docs.abstract: Rising Covid cases have spurred a return to mask-wearing in the U.S. and overseas, at a time when flawed KN95s from China continue to dominate e-commerce sites.
